Title: Remarks on geometric entropy
Authors: J.S.Dowker
Comments: 7p.,uses jyTeX,MUTP/94/2
Journal-ref: Class.Quant.Grav. 11 (1994) L55-L60
\\
  The recently discussed notion of geometric entropy is shown to be related to
earlier calculations of thermal effects in Rindler space. The evaluation is
extended to de Sitter space and to a two-dimensional black hole.
